{"word":"τ᾽","slug":"τ᾽","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n102121\" key=\"t'\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">τ᾽</orth>, apostroph. for <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">τε</itype>, <sense id=\"n102121.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">and.</tr_> </sense> <sense n=\"2\" id=\"n102121.1\" level=\"3\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">τοι</itype> is elided in <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:1:60\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.60</biblScope></bibl>,<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:347\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">347</biblScope></bibl>, also in Aeolic verse, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">θέλω τί τ᾽ εἴπην</quote_> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Sapph.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">28</biblScope></bibl></cit>, cf. <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Alc.\">Alc.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Oxy.\">Oxy.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1788.15</biblScope> </bibl> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\"> ii 9</biblScope></bibl>, but is joined with <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἄν, ἄρα</foreign> by crasis. </sense> <sense n=\"3\" id=\"n102121.2\" level=\"3\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> Attic <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">τό</gen><foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">, τά</foreign> are never elided, but may suffer crasis. </sense> <sense n=\"4\" id=\"n102121.3\" level=\"3\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τὶ</foreign> or <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τί</foreign> can suffer neither elision nor crasis.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}